          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Small Business Tax Relief and Jobs Act of 2017 </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow eligible small businesses an annual tax credit equal to 3.825% of the wages paid to up to three newly hired employees. The wages taken into account with respect to any employee may not exceed $100,000 per year. </p> <p>An &quot;eligible small business&quot; must have under $1.5 million in gross receipts and no more than 20 full-time employees during the preceding taxable year. </p>]]></text>
